<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-08-01T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-08-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="785" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00/673a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-01T12:00:00-04:00">August 1,
                                1931—noon</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>32. Your 84, July 28, 11 a.m. When will elections be called as provided
                            in Article 66 of the Constitution?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
